{%- endfor %}
{%- else %}
No retrieved contexts were available for attribution analysis.
{%- endif %}

### LIME-style Prompt Attribution

*Which prompt sentences contributed most to the output's vocabulary?*

Method: Leave-One-Out (LOO) attribution inspired by LIME (Ribeiro et al. 2016).
Each sentence's score equals the drop in TF-IDF cosine similarity when it is
removed.  Positive = influential; negative = introduced irrelevant vocabulary.
95% bootstrap confidence intervals (200 samples) indicate score stability.

**Baseline similarity (output vs. full prompt):** {{ "%.4f" | format(lime_attribution.baseline_sim) }}
